<HEADLINE> Russian Duma Approves 1998 Budget in First Reading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The Russian State Duma lower
house of parliament on Thursday passed the 1999 budget plan in the
first reading.
</P>
<P>
The draft budget was supported by 303 Duma deputies, far
exceeding the required 226 votes. Sixty-five lawmakers voted
against.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Yevgeny Primakov, who earlier threatened to quit
if the draft was rejected, said the approval was very important
for his cabinet because it is an indication of political support,
Interfax reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
