<HEADLINE> Baby Abandoned Revived in Paris </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 24 (Xinhua) -- A new-born baby, who was
abandoned in a restroom of a great Parisian department store on
Sunday has been revived, reported Agence France-Presse (AFP)
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
AFP quoted Robert Debre of the Assistance Publique emergency
medical aid organization as saying that it was a ``miracle'', as
the baby was half dead when being sent to hospital.
</P>
<P>
The mother of the baby has been found and arrested by police.
She will be brought to court to face questioning by a judge.
</P>
