<HEADLINE> Christmas Shoppings Run up in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Christmas shopping is running up
its rhythm belately in the French capital, with a four percent up
in sales volume in major Parisian department stores so far this
year than last year.
</P>
<P>
Over the past three weeks, the big Parisian department stores
saw the same sales figures as last year, but since Thursday
morning, big shops like the Galeries Lafayette and Printemps have
been seeing an abrupt rise in sales.
</P>
<P>
Toys, books, pens, stationeries, fashion accessories, and other
festival gifts are selling quickly, said management of the shops,
who are expecting greater amount of sales from now till around the
New Year's Day.
</P>
<P>
Other commodities which are selling well include sports
equipments, baggages and mobile phones, according to the
Samaritaine department store. 
</P>
</TEXT>
