<HEADLINE> Ugandan Police Warns of Insecurity During </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
Christmas
</P>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Inspector General of Uganda
Police, John Cossy Odomel, Thursday warned of insecurity caused by
reckless driving and other means during the Christmas season.
</P>
<P>
The police commander made the warning in his Christmas
message, Radio Uganda reported.
</P>
<P>
He cautioned motorists and the general public to guard
against over-loading, speeding and drunken driving and asked
traffic police to deal with offenders firmly and decisively.
</P>
<P>
People were advised to carry money in a safe manner, and
traders reminded that armed guards can be provided on request to
ensure safe transportation of cash.
</P>
<P>
In his message, Resident District Commissioner Kampala
Serapio Karahsani advised parents to avoid sending young children
out to buy drinks for the family or to allow them to stay out
merry making until late.
</P>
<P>
There is report saying that there will be increasing cases of
crime during the Christmas season. 
</P>
