<HEADLINE> Romania: Program to Restructure Army Forces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, December 24 (Xinhua) -- A program-framework has been
finalized this week regarding the reform process of Romanian army
during the next period of time. The document was forwarded to the
Supreme Council of Defense to be discussed and endorsed during its
January 1999 session.
</P>
<P>
The framework program includes short- (1999-2000), medium-
(2001-2005) and long-term (2006-2010) objectives of this process,
the missions and the structure of forces, the main provisions of
the programs to train troops and headquarters, to modernize the
capacity of equipments so as to provide normal conditions for
activities intended to assure Romania's defense and military
security and gradual integration within the North Atlantic
Alliance's military structures.
</P>
<P>
According to provisions in this project, the process of
reducing the forces, the number of headquarters and big units will
continue, to create smaller army forces but with a higher mobility
and better trained and equipped, able to fight against new risks
and threats.
</P>
<P>
The framework-program will assure the concentration of human
material and financial resources in a smaller number of units
while increasing their degree of efficiency, both for missions
specific for the defense of Romania's territory and for
participation in humanitarian missions or to support peace, in
conformity with international agreements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
