Union's unabated efforts to sustain Romania's integration,"
Fotiadis said.
</P>
<P>
Fotiadis also announced that three more PHARE regional
programs will be in place, with Romania among its beneficiaries.
</P>
<P>
One of them is the "Program for Nuclear Safety" and
stipulates the allocation of 700,000 ECU for Romania to review the
earth-quake proof systems of the Cernavoda nuclear power plant
situated in south-eastern Romania.
</P>
<P>
The European Union allotted Romania 118 million ECU in 1997 and
158 million ECU in 1998. 
