<HEADLINE> More Illegal Weapons Recovered in Uganda in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 24 (Xinhua) -- A senior Ugandan police
officer said that more illegal weapons have been recovered
in Kampala district in 1998 than in 1997.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed Thursday by Ochom Edward, the regional Criminal
Investigation Department (CID) officer of the district, when he
addressed CID staff in the region, Radio Uganda reported
in the evening.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, the police have recovered 30 sub-machine guns, 47
pistols and nine other guns, he said.
</P>
<P>
They also recovered 1,157 ammunitions of sub-machine guns, 370
ammunitions of other guns and four stick grenades.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, however, the police recovered 12 sub-machine guns, 19
pistols and four other guns.
</P>
<P>
The police commander, who was recently promoted from senior
superintendent to assistant commissioner, admitted that the year
1998 has been rough for his department due to the problem of bomb
attacks in the capital city. 
</P>
