Thursday in a secret meeting over differences over the movement's
future strategy.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, held at the State Duma, or lower house of
parliament, was chaired by NDR leader Viktor Chernomyrdin, the
former prime minister, Itar-Tass reported.
</P>
<P>
Boris Kuznetsov, Shokhin's deputy in the NDR faction, was to
act as the interim leader.
</P>
<P>
Shokhin, who opened the meeting, said he increasingly disagrees
with Chernomyrdin's views on the prospects of the movement and
ways to rejuvenate it.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin said that the issue of a new leader of the faction
will be tackled after the New Year holidays when the State Duma
starts its Spring session, Tass reported.
</P>
<P>
"Our Home Is Russia must become the chief party of the Russian
provinces," Shokhin wrote in a document prepared for discussion.
</P>
<P>
He proposed a motto describing "the NDR of yesterday as the
party of power, the NDR of today - the party of regions and the
NDR of tomorrow as the party of regional authorities," Interfax
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The news agency said Tuesday that Nikita Mikhalov, a filmmaker
heading the Russian Cinematographic Workers Union, might replace
Shokhin as chairman of the NDR faction. 
