<HEADLINE> Anniversary of Message to Taiwan Compatriots Marked in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scholars specializing
in Taiwan studies said here today that the peaceful reunification
of the motherland has become an irresistible historical trend and
called for efforts to overcome obstacles inside and outside the
Taiwan island to the realization of the reunification cause.
</P>
<P>
At a forum held by the Taiwan Studies Society to mark the 20th
anniversary of the issuing of the Message to Compatriots in
Taiwan, participants reviewed the cross-straits exchanges in the
past two decades in the fields of politics, culture, economy,
trade and transportation.
</P>
<P>
They held the Chinese mainland has adopted active measures in
boosting the cross-straits ties since the issuing of the
message.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the 1997 cross-straits trade volume
amounted to 19.84 billion U.S. dollars, which is 256.6 times the
1978 figure.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, some 13 million Taiwan compatriots have visited the
mainland, with over 70,000 people in the mainland touring the
island.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Wanxin, vice-chairman of the Taiwan Studies Society, said
the historic message has brought significant effect on the
relations across the Taiwan Straits, and both sides have come to
political dialogues from the past military confrontation.
</P>
<P>
The Huangpu Military Academy Alumni Association also held a
forum today in Beijing to mark this event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
