<HEADLINE> Zhuhai to Enhance Ties with Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Huang Longyun, Party
Secretary of the Zhuhai Special Economic Zone (SEZ), today stressed
the importance of the city's future ties with Macao, saying that
strengthened cooperation between the two regions will bring about
common prosperity.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the unique position of Macao as an
international free port, free trade zone, and a gateway to Taiwan
and the European Union, is of special significance to the
development of Zhuhai.
</P>
<P>
Huang made the remarks today at the ongoing fourth meeting of
the city's Party Committee, adding that over the past five years,
Zhuhai's gross domestic product (GDP), the net annual income of
township residents and that of peasants have been increasing at an
annual rate of 13 percent, 6 percent and 8 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
