<DOCNO> XIE19981225.0060 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 8 Die of Cholera in Northwest Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Cholera outbreak has claimed
the lives of eight persons in northwestern Gisenyi prefecture
bordering the Democratic Republic of Congo, state-run radio
Rwanda reported late Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
The first cholera cases were registered in the area on
December 3. ''Up to now, eight people have died of the epidemic,
while 109 others are in critical conditions at Kigufi Hospital,''
Director of Health Services in Gisenyi Erasme Sarambuye told
Rwanda News Agency (RNA).
</P>
<P>
He said that most affected is Nyamyumba commune on the shores
of Lake Kivu, especially in the villages of Busoro, Rubona and
Kiraga. Two more cases of cholera have been identified in the
town of Gisenyi.
</P>
<P>
Sarambuye told RNA that emergency measures have been taken to
check he spread of the epidemic, including reinforcing a medical
team at Kigufi, and sensitizing the local population about
boiling the lake water before its consumption.
</P>
<P>
Cholera had seriously hit southwestern Cyangugu District, also
bordering Lake Kivu. Health officials in that prefecture say that
from March to August this year, 1990 cases of cholera had been
registered, with 48 deaths. However, the epidemic is under
control at present, the officials told RNA. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
