<HEADLINE> China Launches CD-ROM in Memory of Mao Zedong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 25 (Xinhua) -- A CD-rom celebrating the life
of Mao Zedong has been produced to mark the 105th anniversary of
the late Chinese leader's birth on December 26.
</P>
<P>
Entitled "Mao Zedong", it introduces Mao Zedong Thought and
many stories of his life through more than 3,000 pictures and some
120 film and TV archives.
</P>
<P>
It also incorporates 20 volumes of Mao's works, a collection
of his poems and calligraphy while promoting the study of
Marxism, Mao Zedong Thought and Deng Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
At a ceremony to launch the CD-rom in Beijing today, Wei
Jianxing, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee, said,
"Deng Xiaoping Theory has inherited and developed Mao Zedong
Thought and pushed Marxism to a new stage of development in
China." 
