<HEADLINE> Shanghai B-Share Index Rebounds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 25 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Stock Market is
showing signs of adjustment this week, with the B-Share index
rebounding slightly over the previous week.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Shanghai Composite Index closed Friday at
1173.91, up 1.56 percent on the previous week.
</P>
<P>
The SSE-30 Index based on 30 blue chip stocks selected from the
more than 300 A-Shares available to domestic investors closed at
2,809.86, up 1.51 percent.
</P>
<P>
The B-Share stock index has had a slight rebound in spite of
the continued decline over the past weeks. It closed today at
29.13, up 6.59 on the previous week.
</P>
<P>
The trade volume for funds stood at 578 million yuan (about 72
million U.S. dollars), a slight increase over the previous week,
with 16 of the 19 listed funds yielding an increase.
</P>
<P>
Trading on the bond market hit 43.17 billion yuan (about 5.4
billion U.S. dollars), down more than three billion yuan on the
previous week.
</P>
<P>
However, market observers said that the slight rebound of the
stock market index this week will hardly help avert the continued
declines over a short period of time. 
</P>
