<HEADLINE> Hydropower Station Built in Hunan Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, December 25 (Xinhua) -- A hydropower station with a
total installed capacity of 270,000 kilowatts began operation
today on the Yuanshui River in central China's Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
The Lingjintan hydropower station will generate 1.23 billion
kilowatt-hours of electricity a year. In addition, it will help
store floodwater and prevent floods along with the large
hydropower station at Wuqiangxi on the upper reaches of the
Yuanshui, a tributary of the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
The major generating facilities at the Lingjintan power station
have been built with the loans from the Asian Development Bank,
while other investment has been drawn from large foreign companies
through international bidding. 
