along the Israeli-Lebanese border were wounded Wednesday during a
rocket attack launched by the pro-Iranian resistance group
Hezbollah, or Party of God.
</P>
<P>
The attack was a retaliation for an Israeli air strike that
killed a Lebanese woman and six of her seven children on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Since Israel set up a buffer zone in south Lebanon in 1985
after two invasions, there have been frequent clashes between
Israeli soldiers and guerrilla groups, who fight to oust Israeli
troops from Lebanon. 
