<HEADLINE> Mao Reference Book on Mao Zedong Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 25 (Xinhua) -- A valuable and comprehensive
six-volume reference work on the life of the late Chinese leader
Mao Zedong has been published to mark the 105th anniversary of his
birth which falls on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
It is made up in three, two volume, parts: a biography,
the 'works' and the 'thoughts' of the great Chinese revolutionary
and founder of New China.
</P>
<P>
The biographical section chronicles important events in his
life through to his death in 1976. The section focused on his
'works' incorporates a selection of Mao's writings in digest
form. Mao Zedong's Thoughts are covered under five categories:
philosophy, politics, economics, culture and education, and
military matters.
</P>
<P>
The reference work also includes about 800 photographs and
examples of Chairman Mao's original handwritten letters from
different periods in his life.
</P>
<P>
The beautifully designed and bound book includes three extra
commemorative souvenirs for purchasers, a three video-compact disc
set about Chairman Mao, a gold-coated souvenir Chairman Mao badge
and a collection of special cards depicting his life.. 
</P>
</TEXT>
