<P>
BEIJING, December 25 (Xinhua) -- European Union will provide
100,000 Swiss francs as disaster-relief funds to an earthquake-hit
area in south China's Yunnan Province, the Red Cross Society of
China (RCSC) announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The funds via the International Federation of Red Cross and Red
Crescent Societies will be spent on quilts, tents and other
necessities for residents in Ninglang Yi Autonomous County, which
was jolted by two quakes measuring 5.0 and 6.2 degrees on the
Richter scale on November 19.
</P>
<P>
An aiding plan has been drafted by representatives of EU and
the International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent
Societies, who have just concluded a visit to the area, said Wu
Qiusha, a RCSC working staff.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, the RCSC has allocated 200,000 yuan to the area,
and will accept a donation of 530,000 yuan from the Hong Kong Red
Cross Society, Wu said.
</P>
<P>
Strong quakes have hit Ninglang, a poor county in remote
mountainous area of Yunnan, for four times this year, killing five
persons and injuring more than 1,200. About 120,000 houses
collapsed, causing a direct economic loss as high as 500 million
yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
