<HEADLINE> Collectors' Edition of Mao's Works Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- A specially stitched and bound
collectors edition of the Selected Works of Mao Zedong has been
published in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
It commemorates the 105th anniversary of the birth of the late
Chinese leader on December 26th and features the second edition
of his Selected Works first published by the People's Publishing
House in June 1991.
</P>
<P>
It represents the essence of Mao's thoughts and is printed on
Xuanzhi, a high quality paper especially good for traditional
Chinese painting and calligraphy, which is made in east China's
Xuancheng.
</P>
<P>
The new edition is packaged in either wooden or paper boxes and
was published with approval from the Party Literature Research
Center of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China
(CPC), and the State Press and Publication Administration. 
