martyrs similar to those in the 1991 Gulf War, which in Baghdad's
point of view is a U.S-led aggression on Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The Gulf War was set off by Iraq's invasion of Kuwait in August
1990.
</P>
<P>
The meeting lauded the Russian parliament for having adopted an
unbinding resolution on unilateral lifting of U.N. sanctions
against Iraq, which have been in place for more than eight years.
</P>
<P>
