<HEADLINE> China Becomes World's Biggest Leather Producer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 25 (Xinhua) -- China has now become the
world's largest leather and leather products producer following
twenty years' rapid development, the China Leather Industry
Association announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Latest figures from the association show that China currently
has 2,100 tanneries, 6,200 leather shoes factories and 1,500
leather clothing manufacturers, capable of producing more than 100
million pieces of hide, 2.4 billion pairs of shoes and some 80
million items leather clothes a year.
</P>
<P>
By the year 2010, those figures are expected to double,
with three to five international brands emerging, said an
association official.
</P>
<P>
It is only after 1990 when the leather industry, as a
labor-intensive industry, was transferred from developed
countries to developing ones that China become an international
leather processing and marketing center.
</P>
<P>
However, insiders pointed out that a number of problems still
remain unsettled in the industry, such as a limited capacity of
processing high-grade leather products, difficulties in absorbing new
techniques and the pollution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
