<HEADLINE> China's Real Estate Climate Continues to Improve </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 25 (Xinhua) -- China's real estate index,
which indicates the industry's health, was 103.65 points in the
January-November period, up 4.23 points from the same period last
year and 0.04 point from that in the January-October period, the
National Statistics Bureau and the China Business Climate
Monitoring Center reported today.
</P>
<P>
The bureau said this indicated the stability of the overall
climate of the industry.
</P>
<P>
In the period, indexes for real estate project completions,
land sales and newly-developed land were rising.
</P>
<P>
Since March, the floor space of completed real estate projects
has been growing steadily. In the past eleven months, the country
completed real estate projects with a total floor space of 72.7
million square meters, up by 20 percent over last year's same
period.
</P>
<P>
Though the drop in the index for housing prices may adversely
affect the climate for the industry, it helped apartment sales,
said the bureau. 
</P>
