<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Booming Private Economy in South China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Up to date, the number of
private businesses in southernmost China island province of Hainan
has reached more than 130,000, accounting for 35.6 percent of the
total number of Hainan's enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Since the province of Hainan was founded ten years ago, private
economy has witnessed rapid development, with the number of
registered private businesses jumping by 15 percent and it's fixed
assets investment and GDP rising by ten percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
According to local statistics, tax turned in by private
businesses accounted for 38 percent of the total amount of
Hainan. They employ 380,000 people, 30.6 percent of the total
urban employees.
</P>
<P>
In some counties and cities, such as Qionghai, Wenchang and
Sanya, the tax revenue assessed from private businesses have made
up more than 85 percent of the local financial income. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
