<HEADLINE> Iraq Denies Reports of Explosion in Baghdad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, December 25 (Xinhua) -- The Iraqi Information Ministry
on Friday denied news reports that an explosion occurred in
Baghdad early Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
Around 1 a.m. local time Friday (2200 GMT Thursday), sirens
wailed in Baghdad and woke up residents.
</P>
<P>
In a statement carried by the Iraqi News Agency, a spokesman of
the ministry said the sound was caused by a violation of the sound
barrier made by an Iraqi plane.
</P>
<P>
During the four nights of U.S.-British air strikes against Iraq
which came to an end last Saturday, desperate sirens repeatedly
shrieked in the capital to warn people of the incoming missiles.
</P>
