<HEADLINE> Asia's Largest Automobile Race Track Being Built In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, December 25 (Xinhua) -- the Chinese State General
Administration of Sport has given approval to an international
automobile race track in Chengdu, the capital of southwest China's
Sichuan province.
</P>
<P>
The 410-million-yuan race ground will cover 2.5-sq-km and will
be built in three stages. It will become the largest multi-purpose
automobile race track in Asia and is expected to give a boost to
tourism here.
</P>
<P>
Three cities in China have got approval for automobile race
tracks. One is Zhuhai city in south China's Guangdong Province,
the other is in the north China port city of Tianjin, which has
begun construction. 
