<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Mass Produce Lithium Ion Battery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 25 (Xinhua) -- China is building its first
lithium ion storage battery plant in this northern port city with
the approval of the State Development Planning Commission.
</P>
<P>
Invested by Tianjin Lishen Battery Co., Ltd. the
280-million-yuan facility is scheduled for operation by the end
of next year, when it will be able to produce five million pieces
of the "green" battery.
</P>
<P>
The production technology is developed by the Tianjin Power
Supply Research Center, and the quality of the product can reach
or near international standards. The center started the research
of lithium ion battery in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Lithium ion battery, known as a green energy, has been widely
used in electronic devices nowadays for its high storage capacity
and small weight and size. At present, only Japan can produce
such battery in big batches.  
</P>
</TEXT>
