<HEADLINE> Navigation Channel Construction Of Southern Chinese Port Under Way </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a sea
navigation channel in the western part of the port of Shenzhen in
China's Guangdong Province is now under way.
</P>
<P>
An office for the Tonggu navigation project has been
established, for the important project that connects Shenzhen and
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The proposed Tonggu channel will run from Tonggu Island at the
mouth of the Pearl River to the northwest of Dahao Island and will
be a deep-water channel on the western part of Shenzhen's port.
</P>
<P>
It is listed as an important construction project of the state
for the 1996-2000 period approved by the State Development
Planning Commission in July 1997. 
