<HEADLINE> Shandong to Double Efforts to Develop Electronic Info Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 25 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province
has decided to make electronic information sector its leading
industry in five years.
</P>
<P>
Priority will be given to the development of computers,
telecommunications, software applicable to information networking,
and network telecommunications, according to a provincial official.
</P>
<P>
As planned, Shandong's industrial output value and sales income
from manufacturing of electronic equipment such as computers,
telecommunications and audio-visual equipment and new instruments
and materials will reach 80 billion yuan by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Shandong will also make efforts to develop software applicable
to network engineering and telecommunications as well as software
related to the Internet and support software, the official
said. He added that software output is expected to exceed 1.2
billion yuan by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that Shandong's electronic information
industry has been growing very rapidly in recent years, with the
sectoral output reaching 21.6 billion yuan and sales hitting 13.8
billion yuan in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Currently more than 200 enterprises and institutions are
engaged in the electronic information industry, with combined
fixed assets valued at 5.4 billion yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
