<HEADLINE> Zhejiang-Canada Cooperation Has Huge Potential </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, December 25 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang
Province and Canada have much potential for bilateral cooperation,
according to a senior provincial official.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang and Canada can further cooperation in fields such as
agriculture, animal husbandry, environmental protection, and
mineral resources, Tang Jinchun, member of the Standing Committee
of the Zhejiang Provincial People's Congress, said after a visit to
Canada recently.
</P>
<P>
"We can import fine crop and animal species, wheat, barley,
potash fertilize, and pulp from Canada, while our textile
enterprises, paper mills and oil refineries can cooperate with
Canadian companies in environmental protection," Tang said.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that currently some 180 enterprises in
Zhejiang have developed trade relations with Canada. Zhejiang's
imports from Canada last year included 10,000 tons of copper ore,
12,000 tons of barley, and 30,000 tons of pulp.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 140 Canadian companies have invested a total of 240
million US dollars in Zhejiang. Fourteen Canadian companies
invested in Zhejiang in the first nine months of this year alone,
with contracted investment totaling 16.88 million US dollars.
</P>
