<HEADLINE> Philippines to Expand Job Matching System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 25 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines will expand its
computerized job matching system to include its embassies in
countries where there is a huge concentration of overseas Filipino
workers (OFWs).
</P>
<P>
With the initial success of the Phil-Jobnet system, the
government and its partners want to extend their services to OFWs,
the Philippine News Agency said Friday.
</P>
<P>
When the Phil-Jobnet is connected with Philippine embassies,
the agency said, embassy officials can help OFWs find jobs in the
Philippines once they decide to return home for good.
</P>
<P>
At present, there are over 4.5 million OFWs working in Asia,
the Middle East and other regions. The OFWs earn more than 6
billion U.S. dollars annually.
</P>
<P>
With Phil-Jobnet, the agency said, job vacancies will be
announced from time to time to allow job-seekers to choose
positions they deem suitable to their qualifications.
</P>
<P>
Phil-Jobnet is a free job matching system that provides data on
available jobs nationwide on the Internet, the global depository
of information in cyberspace.
</P>
<P>
The system is presently available at Public Employment Service
Offices (PESOs) in municipal town halls in Metro Manila. The
government expects other provinces and cities to link up with the
job-matching system as soon as their respective Internet
connections are operational. 
</P>
</TEXT>
