<HEADLINE> Shanghai Has First Luxury Elderly Care Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai has launched a
massive campaign to upgrade its elderly care centers and the
first one built up to the standard of a three-star hotel was put
into use Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Songjiang Care Center, which cost 38 million
yuan, is divided into living quarters capable of accommodating
250 people, and areas for medical treatment and entertainment. It
is equipped with up-to-date facilities and staffed with
professional doctors and nurses.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai leads other big Chinese cities in entering an old-
age society with an aged population of 2.3 million, accounting
for 17.8 percent of the city's total.
</P>
<P>
There are in Shanghai 385 care centers of various kinds, which
can accommodate 16,000 people, making up a mere 0.66 percent of
the elderly group.
</P>
<P>
The city government predicted that about four percent of the
city's aged group would like to spend their remaining lives in
care centers, and is encouraging more individuals and companies
to invest in building care centers for the elderly.  
</P>
