<P>
The growth rate of the overseas-funded retailers led those of
state, collectively-owned and private retailing enterprises by
10.6 percent, 7.3 percent and 3.14 percent, respectively,
according to the latest report from Guangzhou's Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, overseas investors have shown increasing
enthusiasm for Guangzhou, the major seaport of south China. Ten
more foreign-funded enterprises established footholds in the city
in the first half this year, bringing the total number of
foreign-funded commercial enterprises to 496.
</P>
<P>
With the establishment of more foreign enterprises, a number of
convenient supermarkets, chain stores and other modern shops have
emerged, where prices are low and profits are high. The emergence
of these stores also has greatly stimulated local demand.  
</P>
</TEXT>
