<HEADLINE> Many Chinese Don't Know Who Is Christ on Christmas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 25 (Xinhua) -- More and more Chinese people
are celebrating Christmas, but a survey found that over 60 percent
of them don't know the meaning of Christmas and who on earth Jesus
Christ is.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Morning Post questioned in Jinan, capital of East
China's Shandong Province, nearly 50 people who bought cakes for
Christmas on their knowledge about Christmas and Jesus Christ, and
was startled to find that 34 of them responded "I don't know,"
"I'm not quite clear" or simply retorted, "Who cares?"
</P>
<P>
An accountant, identified as Mr. Li from "Orient Company," said
that he's celebrated Christmas since he was ten, believing
"Christmas is an elegant upper-class activity in the West, a day
for civilized people only and those who don't celebrate Christmas
are definitely dropouts of the society."
</P>
<P>
The newspaper found that this attitude and knowledge about
Christmas also exist among government staff members, businessmen
and teachers.
</P>
<P>
Reporters of the Beijing newspaper stopped a
fashionably-dressed young man and a young woman on the way. They
had just bought a bag of small candles and claimed them as
students.
</P>
<P>
Asked if it is fun to celebrate Christmas, the woman answered,
"Sure, every western festival is fun and exotic."
</P>
<P>
Liu Long, a middle school student, suggested to Beijing Morning
Post reporters that China should abolish the Spring Festival, the
most important Chinese festival, and let all Chinese celebrate
Christmas.
</P>
<P>
The reason he dislikes the Spring Festival is that the festival
is too provincial.
</P>
<P>
A retired professor, who asked to be named as Guo, was adamant
about preserving Chinese festivals while showing a liberal stand
toward Western festivals.
</P>
<P>
"Chinese should take the quintessence of Western festivals
and discard the waste and rough things," he said. "We shouldn't
celebrate a Western festival in a distorted way." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
