<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Witnesses Negative Growth of Electricity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Electricity generation and
consumption in many parts of China declined this year for the
first time in two decades, according to today's Economic
Information Daily.
</P>
<P>
In the first eleven months, electricity generation and
consumption in Shaanxi and Sichuan provinces, Chongqing and
Shanghai municipalities, and Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region dropped
markably, by 10 percent in the worst case.
</P>
<P>
Northeast Electric Power Group, a leading electricity supplier
in northeastern China, generated 87.6 billion kwh of electricity
in the first ten months this year, 2.4 billion kwh less than the
same period last year, and its sales fell by three billion kwh to
83 billion kwh.
</P>
<P>
Experts attribute the shrinking electricity market in
northeast China to the insufficient operations of industrial
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
This summer's destructive flooding is another major factor.
Electricity consumption of farmers in Jilin and Liaoning provinces
has dropped by 28 percent and 18.4 percent, respectively.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
