<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Four navy vessels were lost
this year in confrontation with the Sea Tigers of the Liberation
Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE), naval sources said Friday.
</P>
<P>
However, the navy has been able to inflict considerable damages
on Sea Tigers, sources said.
</P>
<P>
According to records maintained at the Navy headquarters,
approximately 415 LTTE rebels had been killed in confrontations
with naval troops in 1997 and 1998.
</P>
<P>
The sources said among the dead were hard-core rebels holding
the ranks of colonels and lieutenant colonels. He placed the LTTE
craft (mostly fiber glass dinghies) destroyed as a result of naval
action at 106 and damaged at 121.
</P>
<P>
During the same period 38 navy vessels had been damaged in
confrontations, they said.
</P>
<P>
They also said that 55 navy personnel were killed this year, 64
placed missing in action and 94 wounded.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been fighting a 15-year-old war against
the government for a separate state in the north and east of the
country. 
