<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liaoning Reports Record High Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, December 25 (Xinhua) -- An upturn in economic growth
in Liaoning Province, which saw a record high of 8.6 percent in
November, is attributed to the impact of the state's positive
financial and monetary policies.
</P>
<P>
One of China's traditional industrial bases in the northeast,
the province's growth had dipped from 7.7 percent in March to 5.1
percent in August, partly due to the Asian financial crisis and
the devastating summer floods.
</P>
<P>
Pundits noted, however, that since September the economy has
begun to bottom out.
</P>
<P>
According to a provincial government official the state policy
to stimulate and increase domestic demand has yielded positive
results in Liaoning. The province invested 59.77 billion yuan
(about 7.47 billion U.S. dollars) in fixed assets in the
January-November period this year, an increase of 4.7 percent on a
year-on-year basis.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the real estate sector has become a new popular
investment hot-spot in the province after the State Council
launched a reform in the housing distribution system this year.
</P>
<P>
The province injected a total of 10.84 billion yuan into the
sector in the 11 months, accounting for 18.1 percent of the
province's total investment.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to other state policies which ban the artificial cutting
of prices for industrial products in order to improve competition,
the prices of 13 major products has remained stable and even
increased in November, compared to October.
</P>
<P>
The consumer market is brisk, with total retail sales of
consumer goods topping 140 billion yuan in the January-November
period, up 11.1 percent in real terms over the same period of last
year.
</P>
<P>
Thus by taking full advantage of the state's macroeconomic
policies, Liaoning will be pushing forward its reform of
state-owned enterprises, improving competition and market share,
so as to ensure its objective of an eight percent economic growth
for the year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
