<HEADLINE> China Plans Major Land Resource Survey for 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 25 (Xinhua) -- China is preparing for a major
survey of land, mining, and ocean resources in 1999 to fill in
blank spaces in its basic geological survey.
</P>
<P>
The survey is expected to update basic maps, charts, and graphs
and the potential of nationwide mineral resources by 2002,
according to the Ministry of Land Resources.
</P>
<P>
It will also study the potential of resources of major
groundwater areas and major water-shortage areas in northwestern
and southwestern China.
</P>
<P>
There will be a nationwide environmental geology survey to
study the distribution of major geological disasters, help plan
for and prevent calamities, and provide a warning for disasters.
</P>
<P>
The plan is to complete the all-round land resource survey by
2010, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Chengsong, vice-minister of land resources, said that the
new survey differs from segmented land surveys of the past, and
will contribute to the development of the Chinese economy and
society.  
</P>
