<HEADLINE> Chinese Economist Predicts Accelerated Growth for Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 25 (Xinhua) -- A latest State Administration
of Internal Trade report predicts that China will accelerate the
pace of economic growth by the second quarter next year.
</P>
<P>
Domestic consumer demand is expected to increase, but the
current situation of oversupply of some consumer goods, especially
medium- and low-grade ones, is not likely to improve much.
</P>
<P>
To deal with the negative impact of sluggish domestic demand
and weak exports caused by the Asian financial crisis, the Chinese
government has taken a number of policies this year, with three
consecutive interest rates cuts, increased spending on
infrastructure, and increased bank loans and export tax rebates.
</P>
<P>
The positive effects of these policies on the national economy
will become more apparent in the second quarter next year, and
capital goods producers are likely to benefit from state policies
more than enterprises focusing on consumer goods, the report
said.  
</P>
