<HEADLINE> Albanian Women Paid Less Than Men </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, December 24 (Xinhua) -- Albanian women are paid less
than men for the same job, according to figures reported by the
country's national statistics bureau INSTAT on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
While the average salary for an administration employee was
14,207 leks (about 100 U.S. dollars) for 1997, the average for a
man working in a public administration was 16,685 leks and 13,547
leks for a woman.
</P>
<P>
The difference is also evident in higher positions. While the
average wage for an official was 26,079 leks, it was 27,903 leks
if the official was a man and 25,442 leks if the official was a
woman.
</P>
<P>
INSTAT said the gap exists in the private sector too.
</P>
<P>
Surveys conducted in private manufacturing operations in
1994-1996 show that a man was paid some 13,000 leks while a woman
some 9,000 leks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
