<HEADLINE> Bus Accident Kills Eight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, December 24 (Xinhua) -- At least eight people were
killed on Thursday when a bus overturned on the Garden State
Parkway in New Jersey, U.S.A., police said.
</P>
<P>
The bus was carrying 23 people from New York to Atlantic City.
The 52-year-old driver lost control at a section 25 miles
southwest of Brooklyn, a borough of New York.
</P>
<P>
The bus went through a guard-rail and flipped over to rest on
the driver's side, with some passengers caught trapped for hours
between 10:00 and 11:00 am local time.
</P>
<P>
The accident killed 8 passengers and injured 15, state police
confirmed later.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident was under investigation. Some traced
the snow which has fallen overnight as the trouble-maker. Police
did not take it for sure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
