<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Jobless Number Falls to the Lowest level </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 24 (Xinhua) -- The number of applications
for unemployment benefits fell by 13,000 last week to the lowest
level in 17 months, the U.S. Labor Department reported on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It said that a total 287,000 people sought jobless pay from
state governments, down from 300,000 in the prior week. It is the
lowest since the week of July 26, 1997, when there were 276,000
people seeking jobless pay.
</P>
<P>
Economists said the report combining with the personal income
increase last month added up to a merry Christmas for U.S. working
people and a happy start to the new year. The U.S. economy will
complete eight years of continued growth next March from the last
recession in 1990-1991.  
</P>
</TEXT>
